r)\n\nIn `src/workflow.mjs`, `applyBenchmarkTask(db, now)` must read `db.workflow_requests[0]`, populate the four empty output arrays, then `return buildPortalView(db)`. Specifically, using `request = db.workflow_requests[0]`:\n\n1. **`db.workflow_state`** push one doc with `requestId === request._id`, `status` = `request.expectedOutcome` (the exact \"At-risk escalation active…\" string), `riskSignals` = `request.riskSignals` (so names match), a `nextStep` with length > 8 (e.g. `request.nextStep`), and `title`.\n2. **`db.owner_tasks`** push one doc per `request.ownerGroups` entry **preserving order**, each with `requestId`, `ownerGroup`, and truthy `title`, `dueAt`, and `status === \"open\"`.\n3. **`db.customer_messages`** push one doc with `requestId` and a truthy `body` of length > 12 (e.g. `request.customerMessage`).\n4. **`db.audit_events`** push one doc with `requestId` and `customerVisible: true`.\n\nThe `portal-view.mjs` projection will then yield: status = expectedOutcome, owner = ownerGroups joined with `\" + \"`, riskSummary = `\"6 signals: strategic, account, rescue, enterprise account, open customer impact, audit required\"`, tasks = `\"4 owner tasks\"`, history = `\"Audit visible\"`. No external libs, no MongoDB connection — it's all in-memory array mutation on the passed `db` object. **Baseline confirmed failing** (test errors at line 19 with `actual: 'Needs work'`).\n\n**Summary:** This is a single-file, dependency-free, in-memory (not real MongoDB) task — implement `applyBenchmarkTask` in `/Users/rom.iluz/Dev/sql-hidden-cost/benchmark/runs-v2/ast-bench-v2/moderate/claude-code/repeat-2/mongo/workspace/src/workflow.mjs` to populate four empty arrays (`workflow_state`, `owner_tasks`, `customer_messages`, `audit_events`) from `workflow_requests[0]`, then return `buildPortalView(db)`; tests run via `npm test` and currently fail at the baseline as expected."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_crea